'''ABC Great Southern''' is an [[ABC Local Radio]] station based in [[Wagin, Western Australia|Wagin]]. The station broadcasts to parts of the [[Great Southern (Western Australia)|Great Southern]] and [[Wheatbelt (Western Australia)|Wheatbelt]] regions of [[Western Australia]]. This includes the towns of [[Katanning, Western Australia|Katanning]] and [[Narrogin, Western Australia|Narrogin]].
The station began broadcasting as '''6WA''' in 1936. It was originally built solely as a retransmission facility, relaying [[6WF]] from [[Perth (Western Australia)|Perth]] to the greater southwest area of the state. At the time it was the tallest and most powerful transmitter in [[Australia]]. New studios were opened in the town of Wagin in 2003 to provide local programs.
When local programs are not broadcast the station is a relay of [[ABC South Coast]] and [[720 ABC Perth]].
